description.narrative: (Ethiopia): The Health Financing Improvement Program (HFIP).strengthens the health financing functions and systems to support Universal.Health Coverage of essential health care for Ethiopian citizens by reducing.financial barriers, thereby increasing access and self reliance within the.sector. USAID, through this activity, works with the Ministry of Health, the.Ethiopian Health Insurance Agency and other relevant ministries and government.agencies at the federal and sub-national levels toward increased domestic.resource mobilization (DRM) for health, financial risk-protection programs.(Community-Based Health Insurance and Social Health Insurance), and improved.capacity for better financial policies, decision-making and resource.management. This mechanism provides technical assistance to promote increased.DRM, sustainability, and self-reliance of health programs. In FY 2020 HFIP will.focus on further widening of the CBHI coverage in rural areas, roll-out of the.CBHI program to urban cities, adaptation of the CBHI model for scaling-up in.lowland/developing regions, and increased DRM for health and priority Public.Health Programs (such as HIV, TB, Malaria, MCH-FP). Another key activity will.be to support the transition of the 1st Generation Health Financing Reforms.that were designed and implemented within the previous USAID programs to local.entities. The latter would enable regions/city government administrations to.institutionalize the planning, financing, implementation and management of.these reform interventions going forward...... .
